The project selected for this course is “Smart Queue Management System for Banks.”
The project aims to address common issues such as long waiting times, overcrowding, and inefficient customer flow management in bank branches by introducing a digital queue management solution.
This project was chosen because it solves a real-world problem using software engineering principles and demonstrates practical application of system analysis, requirement specification, and design using UML and CASE tools.

Team Formation and Assigned Roles
To ensure systematic development and effective collaboration, the project team was formed with clearly defined roles and responsibilities as follows:
Team Member	Assigned Role	Responsibilities
Aryavardhan Singh Shekhawat	Project Manager	Project planning, task allocation, progress tracking, coordination among team members
Risha Rasheed P M	Documentation Lead	Preparation of SRS, design documents, reports, and maintaining documentation consistency
Khushi R	Lead Developer 1	System design logic, module planning, and technical implementation guidance
Kanan	Lead Developer 2	System design logic, module planning, and technical implementation guidance
Devansh Khare	QA Lead	Requirement verification, review of documents, quality assurance, and validation of system design
These roles ensure clear accountability, efficient workflow, and timely completion of the Smart Queue Management System for Banks project.
